ce:section.ce:para:
The CuNCs and N-CQDs were prepared according to the previous reported literatures (Scheme 1
                        ) (Han et al., 2018; Y. Yang et al., 2020) and further characterized by TEM measurement to verify their as-synthesized nanostructures (Fig. 1
                        ). As presented in Fig. 1A, the TEM image implied that the CuNCs were prepared successfully with a nanoribbon morphology: a mean length of 300–700 nm and a width of ∼ 20 nm, the same as the literature described (Han et al., 2018). Energy dispersive X-ray (EDX) analysis also revealed the existence of Cu, C, F, and S in the assembled CuNCs (Fig. S1). The N-CQDs in Fig. 1B were in a well monodispersed dispersion with a uniform particle size of approximately 4–5 nm. The carbon lattice spacing is calculated to be approximately 2.7 Å from the enlarged lattice structure diagram at the upper left. Additionally, the N-CQDs@CuNCs complex was confirmed by zeta potential analyses, which strongly suggested that the N-CQDs and CuNCs work synergistically to maintain integrity in the fluorescent probe.
